  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6fc7463 2024-01-05T00:21:51.712802723Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nscript had this string in the code: `\\u250c\\u2500\\u2015\\u2015┄┈\\n\"`\r\n\r\n```\r\n forge script script/Example.s.sol --broadcast --private-key $PK --slow --rpc-url $RPC\r\n[⠢] Compiling...\r\n[⠆] Compiling 3 files with 0.8.20The application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  byte index 47 is not a char boundary; it is inside '┄' (bytes 46..49) of `57 |                 \"\\u250c\\u2500\\u2015\\u2015┄┈\\n\"`\r\nLocation: /home/runner/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-6f17d22bba15001f/foundry-compilers-0.1.2/src/artifacts/mod.rs:2084\r\n\r\nThis is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry\r\n```\r\n\r\nEdge case - mitigated by properly escaping all unicode chars.\r\n",
